<http://www.spektrix.com/sidwilliams/event/200402ATTHDDQNRMSVGKGCDJSLLRBHVDS> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "A Cabaret of Legends";
  schema:description """
	This electrifying production, hailed as \"a powerhouse performance\" by the <span class=\"ItalicText\">Edmonton Journal</span>, and a \"BEST OF FEST\" by the <span class=\"ItalicText\">Orlando Sentinel</span>, celebrates the iconic voices that have shaped the world of entertainment. <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">A Cabaret of Legends</span></span> is a thrilling musical journey where Tymisha Harris, with her undeniable charisma and \"vocal fireworks” (<span class=\"ItalicText\">CBC Montreal</span>), pays homage to the greatest performers of all time, from soulful jazz to electrifying pop. Harris, star of the international hit show <span class=\"ItalicText\">Josephine</span>, sings through the generations of black female vocal legends and shares stories of their impact on her personal journey. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Harris has an \"uncanny ability to mimic the voice stylings of the various singers whose songs she performs, whether it’s Billie Holliday or Whitney Houston, without completely losing her own unique qualities\". Audiences can expect a non-stop spectacle of music, dance, and pure entertainment. Critics have praised the show as \"a stunning display of song and history\" and stated, \"you still might be singing...out loud for days after this perfect act of love.\" <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>★★★★★ <span class=\"ItalicText\">“As a standard bearer for almost an entire century of music, you really couldn’t do better than badass burlesque diva Tymisha Harris.”</span> – Edmonton Journal <span><br/></span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Aspiring legendary vocalist Tymisha Harris spent decades performing as Aretha Franklin at Universal Studios and working as a Tina Turner impersonator and tribute artist. She has won dozens of awards for her portrayal of Josephine Baker in the off-Broadway and international hit show “Josephine”, and is a two-time winner of the Orlando Sentinel Critic’s Choice for “Leading Actress, Musical” (one for <span class=\"ItalicText\">Josephine</span>, the other for her embodiment of Billie Holiday in <span class=\"ItalicText\">Lady Day at Emerson’s Bar & Grill</span>). <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In this new, surprisingly personal cabaret, Tymisha talks about her personal journey and those of the legends who influenced her, while she sings some of the most impactful songs from throughout their and her career.
""";
  schema:startDate "2027-04-08T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
