<http://www.spektrix.com/sidwilliams/event/199802ALSCTDJKCDLRDPGCHGPMDDBJGRC> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Bangs, Bobs & Banter: Confessions Of A Hairstylist";
  schema:description """
	A Critics' Choice and Patrons Pick winner at Orlando Fringe and Edmonton Fringe sellout (2024 & 2025), this one-woman comedy brings 10 characters to life. Inspired by true events, it’s a hilarious, heartfelt journey that’s relatable, radiant, and real - a must-see blend of humor and humanity that leaves audiences laughing and moved! <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In this 60-minute comedy, Joanne Rannelli embodies the role of Nikki, a charismatic hairstylist with a knack for storytelling. Drawing inspiration from real-life encounters, Nikki invites the audience into her salon, where a cast of colorful clientele share their sassy, saucy, and scandalous hair-raising secrets. From unreasonable demands to raunchy tales and taboo confessions, Bangs, Bobs & Banter promises to keep audiences entertained and laughing throughout.  <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">“Funny and deeply human, Rannelli’s transformations are so flawless and immersive you forget you’re watching one performer. She doesn’t just act these women, she becomes them.”</span> - The Vibe Hamilton <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">“Impressively polished…Rannelli is a winning performer”</span> - Orlando Weekly <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Credits:</span><span><br/></span>Written & Performed by Joanna Rannelli <span><br/></span>Dramaturg & Directed by Kerry Ipema 
""";
