<http://www.spektrix.com/sidwilliams/event/200001AKDLNNPPQKVCGNTJLPNLGRMLLQP> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Stuart Little";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">By Joseph Robinette, adapted from the novel by E.B. White</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A Carousel Theatre for Young People Production <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">“If you're looking for a fun, family-friendly activity? Stuart Little is sure to charm audiences of all ages — you won't be disappointed!”</span> - Review Vancouver <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This enchanting play, adapted by Joseph Robinette, brings E.B. White's timeless tale to life in this intimate and captivating telling. As Stuart, the endearing little mouse with a great big heart, navigates a world built for humans, the play unfolds with a perfect blend of whimsy and heartwarming moments. Robinette's adaptation skillfully captures the essence of White's original work, highlighting Stuart's courage and resilience in the face of a world not built for such a little mouse. With a delightful mix of humor, adventure, and poignant moments, this play promises an unforgettable theatrical experience for audiences of all ages. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">About Carousel Theatre</span> <span><br/></span>Carousel Theatre for Young People (CTYP) is a gathering place for young people, families and artists to embark on a journey where boundless imagination, a dash of magic and an abundance of play are the recipe for a magical theatrical adventure that has lasting impact. They have been creating theatre for young people since their inception in 1976. Located on Granville Island in the heart of Vancouver, CTYP is Vancouver’s mainstage TYA company.
""";
  schema:startDate "2027-03-04T18:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
